00034 DataspaceLib::~DataspaceLib()
00035 {
00036         t_symbol                **keys = NULL;
00037         long                    numKeys = 0;
00038         long                    i;
00039         DataspaceUnit   *unit;
00040 
00041         hashtab_getkeys(unitHash, &numKeys, &keys);
00042         for(i=0; i<numKeys; i++){
00043                 hashtab_lookup(unitHash, keys[i], (t_object**)&unit);
00044                 delete unit;
00045         }
00046         
00047         if(keys)
00048                 sysmem_freeptr(keys);
00049                 
00050         hashtab_chuck(unitHash);
00051 }

00054 // remember, we are relying on memory passed in for the outputAtoms             
00055 JamomaError DataspaceLib::convert(long inputNumArgs, t_atom *inputAtoms, long *outputNumArgs, t_atom **outputAtoms)
00056 {
00057         double  value[3];       // right now we only handle a maximum of 3 values in the neutral unit passing
00058         long    numvalues;
00059         
00060         if(inUnit->name == outUnit->name){
00061                 *outputNumArgs = inputNumArgs;
00062                 sysmem_copyptr(inputAtoms, *outputAtoms, sizeof(t_atom) * inputNumArgs);
00063         }
00064         else{
00065                 inUnit->convertToNeutral(inputNumArgs, inputAtoms, &numvalues, value);
00066                 outUnit->convertFromNeutral(numvalues, value, outputNumArgs, outputAtoms);
00067         }
00068         return JAMOMA_ERR_NONE;
00069 }

00072 JamomaError DataspaceLib::setInputUnit(t_symbol *inUnitName)
00073 {
00074         if(inUnit && inUnitName == inUnit->name)        // already have this one loaded
00075                 return JAMOMA_ERR_NONE;
00076         else
00077                 return (JamomaError)hashtab_lookup(unitHash, inUnitName, (t_object**)&inUnit);
00078 }

00118 JamomaError jamoma_getDataspace(t_symbol *dataspaceName, DataspaceLib **dataspace)
00119 {       
00120         if(*dataspace){
00121                 if(dataspaceName == (*dataspace)->name)
00122                         return JAMOMA_ERR_NONE; // already have this one, do nothing...
00123                 else{
00124                         delete *dataspace;
00125                         *dataspace = NULL;
00126                 }
00127         }
00128 
00129         // These should be alphabetized
00130         if(dataspaceName == gensym("angle"))
00131                 *dataspace = (DataspaceLib*) new AngleDataspace;
00132         else if(dataspaceName == gensym("color"))
00133                 *dataspace = (DataspaceLib*) new ColorDataspace;
00134         else if(dataspaceName == gensym("distance"))
00135                 *dataspace = (DataspaceLib*) new DistanceDataspace;
00136         else if(dataspaceName == gensym("gain"))
00137                 *dataspace = (DataspaceLib*) new GainDataspace;
00138         else if(dataspaceName == gensym("none"))
00139                 *dataspace = (DataspaceLib*) new NoneDataspace;
00140         else if(dataspaceName == gensym("pitch"))
00141                 *dataspace = (DataspaceLib*) new PitchDataspace;
00142         else if(dataspaceName == gensym("position")) 
00143                 *dataspace = (DataspaceLib*) new PositionDataspace;
00144         else if(dataspaceName == gensym("temperature"))
00145                 *dataspace = (DataspaceLib*) new TemperatureDataspace;
00146         else if(dataspaceName == gensym("time"))
00147                 *dataspace = (DataspaceLib*) new TimeDataspace;
00148         else 
00149                 // Invalid -- default to temperature
00150                 *dataspace = (DataspaceLib*) new TemperatureDataspace;
00151         
00152         return JAMOMA_ERR_NONE;
00153 }

00156 // This function allocates memory -- caller must free it!
00157 void jamoma_getDataspaceList(long *numDataspaces, t_symbol ***dataspaceNames)
00158 {
00159         *numDataspaces = 9; // must be the length of the Dataspace
00160         *dataspaceNames = (t_symbol**)sysmem_newptr(sizeof(t_symbol*) * *numDataspaces);
00161         
00162         // These should be alphabetized
00163         if(*numDataspaces){
00164                 *(*dataspaceNames+0) = gensym("angle");
00165                 *(*dataspaceNames+1) = gensym("color");
00166                 *(*dataspaceNames+2) = gensym("distance");
00167                 *(*dataspaceNames+3) = gensym("gain");
00168                 *(*dataspaceNames+4) = gensym("none");
00169                 *(*dataspaceNames+5) = gensym("pitch");
00170                 *(*dataspaceNames+6) = gensym("position"); 
00171                 *(*dataspaceNames+7) = gensym("temperature");
00172                 *(*dataspaceNames+8) = gensym("time");
00173         }
00174 }
